x= \sqrt{a^2-y^2}
\frac{dx}{dy}= \frac{-y}{\sqrt{a^2-y^2}}
\text{Surface area } S = \int 2\pi x \sqrt{1+\left(\frac{dx}{dy}\right)^2} dy
S=\int_0^{\frac{a}{2}}2\pi \sqrt{a^2-y^2}\sqrt{1+ \frac{y^2}{{a^2-y^2}}} dy
=\int_0^{\frac{a}{2}}2\pi \sqrt{a^2-y^2} \frac{a}{\sqrt{a^2-y^2}}dy 
=\int_0^{\frac{a}{2}}2\pi .a dy
=\pi .a^2
